## âš™ï¸ 1ï¸âƒ£ Laravel Lifecycle â€” *â€œHow does Laravel handle a request?â€*

**Theory (short & powerful):**
When a request hits Laravel:
`index.php â†’ Kernel â†’ Middleware â†’ RouteServiceProvider â†’ Controller â†’ Response â†’ Middleware (reverse) â†’ Client.`

**Real-world example:**
When a user visits `/users`, Laravel bootstraps config, passes request through `VerifyCsrfToken`, `Authenticate`, etc., then resolves the controller and sends the response.
If a request fails `Authenticate`, middleware stops it right there â€” **no unnecessary logic runs**.

âœ… *Pro tip:* Mention that this layered pipeline is what makes Laravel scalable and testable.

