## ğŸ’¾ 9ï¸âƒ£ Storage & Symlink â€” *â€œWhy use `php artisan storage:link`?â€*

**Theory:**
Storage link creates a symbolic link from `public/storage` â†’ `storage/app/public`.
It lets uploaded files be accessible publicly.

**Real-world example:**
When a user uploads a profile image, you store it:

```php
$request->file('avatar')->store('public/avatars');
```

To serve it:
`php artisan storage:link`
Now `/storage/avatars/image.png` is web-accessible.

âœ… *Pro tip:* â€œNever store uploads in `/public` directly â€” always use `storage` for security.â€

