## ğŸš¨ 10ï¸âƒ£ Exception Handling â€” *â€œHow does Laravel handle errors?â€*

**Theory:**
All exceptions go through `app/Exceptions/Handler.php`.
You can customize `render()` and `report()` methods.

**Real-world example:**

```php
public function render($request, Throwable $e)
{
    if ($request->expectsJson()) {
        return response()->json(['error' => $e->getMessage()], 500);
    }
    return parent::render($request, $e);
}
```

âœ… *Pro tip:* â€œAlways format API exceptions for consistency (JSON structure).â€

