## ğŸ§  11ï¸âƒ£ Events & Listeners â€” *â€œWhy event-driven architecture?â€*

**Theory:**
Events decouple actions from consequences.
Listener reacts to event â†’ async or queued execution.

**Real-world example:**
`UserRegistered` event triggers `SendWelcomeEmail` listener.
Even if email fails, user registration still succeeds.

âœ… *Pro tip:* â€œEvents improve scalability and code cleanliness.â€

